# GIMA - MVP Walkthrough üèÄ

The Minimum Viable Product for **GIMA (LinkedIn + Hudl + AI Coach for wheelchair athletes)** has been successfully built! The project uses a Next.js (App Router) foundation coupled with a premium, custom Vanilla CSS UI, strictly avoiding generic frameworks to deliver that "Wow" factor.

## Changes Made & Features Delivered

### 1. Robust Design System
- **Premium Aesthetics:** We implemented a custom design system in [globals.css](file:///c:/Users/USER/Projects/gima/src/app/globals.css) featuring deep dark themes (`#0d0d0d`), glassmorphic panels (`backdrop-filter`), smooth micro-transitions (`0.3s ease`), and a vibrant sports orange (`#ff4500`) primary accent.

### 2. Authentication Flow (MVP Core)
- **Landing Page (`/`)**: A sleek, high-contrast entry pointing users to join as an Athlete or Coach.
- **Role-Based Auth Flow (`/login`, `/register`)**: Beautifully styled form screens managing the mock split logic between what athletes experience vs. what coaches experience.

### 3. Player Dashboard (`/player/dashboard`)
The core athlete profile interface:
- **Stats Card:** Rich, visual metric cards (PPG, APG, RPG, FG%, MIN). 
- **Injury Tracking:** Organized timeline displaying recovery time and real-time medical clearance status.
- **Match History:** A clean data grid showing opponent performance results (W/L badges, Pts, Asts).

### 4. Coach Interface & Affiliation
- **Discovery (`/coach/dashboard`)**: A search and categorization engine for coaches to find wheelchair athletes dynamically. Includes athlete attribute previews (PPG, APG, Sport, Position).
- **Messaging (MVC)**: An interactive [ChatPanel](file:///c:/Users/USER/Projects/gima/src/components/ChatPanel.tsx#5-71) widget available on the player's dashboard to mock direct 1-to-1 communication with potential future affiliated coaches.

### 5. Functional AI API Endpoints
We established independent mock internal Next.js endpoints intended to map to an LLM provider (like OpenAI) later:
- `POST /api/ai/summary`: One-tap AI insights synthesizing the athlete's progression over the season.
- `POST /api/ai/training`: Custom programmatic recovery/drills recommendations tailored for adaptive sports.
- `POST /api/ai/vendor`: AI-based vendor matching for customized titanium frames and carbon-fiber rims.

